monster_blueprint_identity.prompt_template:
You are a creature designer for a fantasy monster-catching game. You are designing the FACTS of a new monster - its lineage and nature. Later steps will give it a personality, so keep this step factual.

========== CONTEXT ==========

--- Where this monster dwells ---
{location_context}

--- This monster's rarity (already decided) ---
{rarity} - design a creature whose concept fits this rarity. Common creatures are everyday wildlife of this world; legendary ones are once-in-a-generation beings.

--- Curated taxonomy: pick ONE domain and ONE kingdom from this tree ---
{taxonomy_options}

========== YOUR TASK ==========
Invent a creature that belongs where it dwells. Choose domain and kingdom FROM THE TREE ABOVE, then INVENT its lower lineage: family (a lineage name), genus (a breed name), species (its full species name). Also give:
- name: the personal name its friends call it
- race_label: a plain-language word for what it looks like (e.g. Beetle, Drake, Sprite)
- party_role: one of {role_options}
- size_class: one of {size_options}
- lifecycle_stage: one of {lifecycle_options}
- creation_mechanism: how it came to exist - one of {creation_options}

========== RESPONSE FORMAT ==========
Respond with ONLY valid JSON in exactly this format:
{{"name": "...", "domain": "...", "kingdom": "...", "family": "...", "genus": "...", "species": "...", "race_label": "...", "party_role": "...", "size_class": "...", "lifecycle_stage": "...", "creation_mechanism": "..."}}

JSON:

monster_blueprint_ecology.prompt_template:
You are a creature designer for a fantasy monster-catching game, detailing how an already-designed creature LIVES.

========== CONTEXT ==========

--- Where this monster dwells ---
{location_context}

--- The creature so far ---
{identity_facts}

========== YOUR TASK ==========
Decide its way of life. Every choice must fit the creature above and where it dwells. Pick ONLY from the allowed values:
- habitat_primary: one of {habitat_options}
- habitat_secondary: list, others of those it also roams (may be empty)
- biomes: list of 1-3 from: {biome_options}
- social_structure: one of {social_options} (social_notes: one short phrase on its social life)
- sustenance: list of 1-2 from: {sustenance_options}
- feeding_style: one of {feeding_options} (diet_notes: one short phrase on what it actually eats)
- sapience: one of {sapience_options} (feral cannot speak at all; bestial understands tone but not words)
- communication: list from: {communication_options}
- elements: list of 0-2 elemental affinities from: {element_options}
- activity_cycle: one of {activity_options}
- Trained class, if any: class_domain one of {class_domain_options_line} or "none" if untrained. If trained, INVENT class_discipline (its school of training) and class_specialization (its signature technique focus).

Class domains explained:
{class_domain_options}

========== RESPONSE FORMAT ==========
Respond with ONLY valid JSON in exactly this format:
{{"habitat_primary": "...", "habitat_secondary": ["..."], "biomes": ["..."], "social_structure": "...", "social_notes": "...", "sustenance": ["..."], "feeding_style": "...", "diet_notes": "...", "sapience": "...", "communication": ["..."], "elements": ["..."], "activity_cycle": "...", "class_domain": "...", "class_discipline": "...", "class_specialization": "..."}}

